edu.cnm.deepdive.android

Interface FluentAsyncTask.Performer<Params,Result>

  • Type Parameters:
    Params - type of input parameters used by the asynchronous task (consumed by perform(Object[])), or Void if no inputs will be used.
    Result - type of result data produced by the basic background processing of the asynchronous task (returned by perform(Object[]), or (usually) Void if the background processing is not intended to return a result.
    Enclosing class:
    FluentAsyncTask<Params,Progress,Result>

    public static interface FluentAsyncTask.Performer<Params,Result>
    Declares a perform(Object[]) method that can be implemented to perform basic background processing in an instance of FluentAsyncTask.
